            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Howl of the Wild pg. 136",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Howl of the Wild",
          "page": 136,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "Though it lacks the distinctive horns of its larger relative the triceratops, the protoceratops is more than capable of holding its own in combat, using its tail to knock enemies to the ground and its sturdy frill to turn away blows.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
